                    "reviewerid": "3212266",
                    "reviewer_name": "Dorothy (Dodie)",
                    "comments": "This is a rare find:  an art-deco gem with beautiful artwork, books and music.  We've stayed here on many occasions.  If you like to cook, or just bring back food to the apartment, this is the place for you:  well-stocked kitchen is an understatement.  And, of course, the location:  you're in the hip Condesa with great restaurants and places to walk in the evening;  and, at the same time you're just across the Insurgentes from Roma Sur where you'll find even better (and cheaper) food in the fondas, puestos, and Mercado Medellin.   If you're lucky enough to be here on a Tuesday, don't miss the Condesa tianguis, the great weekly market about 10 minutes walk away.  Or, walk north into Roma Norte for more great restaurants and entirely different feel with its Porfiriano architecture.  In the past, we've used taxis and the metro, but Uber now makes it even easier to get around:  depending on traffic, you are 20 minutes from the Centro and even closer to the museums in Chapultepec.  Nick is a great host:  easy to reach and always a source for good eats in Mexico City and elsewhere in Mexico."
