                    "reviewerid": "2886775",
                    "reviewer_name": "Jose",
                    "comments": "Loved staying in the upper studio in Coyoacan. My partner and I are both artists and this was a perfect location for those interested in the history of Frida Kahlo and the neighborhood she called home. \r\n\r\nThe staff were very helpful and friendly. The space was full of light and charming. The best part was the small patio in the back and access to the roof space where I spent my mornings sketching and planning out the day's activities. \r\n\r\nIn terms of its location and access to other parts of the city, I wouldn't say it was super convenient. The closest Metro stop is realistically 20 minutes away, and once you reach the metro it can take some time to get to certain parts of the city like the Zocalo and Chapultepec. However, we did not have any trouble navigating and exploring the city using the recommended secure taxi and other safe transportation apps (Uber just launched in the city), which were very reasonably priced. The neighborhood was quiet and safe at night. We spent several evenings walking to the plaza where we enjoyed great cuisine and a lively atmosphere.  \r\n\r\nI would definitely consider staying here again on a future trip. "
