                    "date": "2013-11-01",
                    "reviewerid": "1692914",
                    "reviewer_name": "Jane & Brad",
                    "comments": "Unfortunately we didn\u2019t meet Trisha, as she wasn\u2019t in Mexico when we arrived, but she made arrangements for us to be met by a staff member, Isabel, who was charming & helpful. Trisha kindly agreed to us dropping our luggage at the apartment before check-in time, which was really helpful to us. \r\nThe apartment is decorated in a simple stylish manner - the use of colour is just beautiful - exactly as shown in the photos. The only thing we didn\u2019t realize from the photos was that the apartment is on the second floor, accessed by an external spiral staircase (not a problem for us, but may be something to consider if you have big luggage or mobility problems). We found the apartment was clean & quiet; the bed was very comfortable & the water pressure in the shower was great. Loved the way the bathroom was decorated! We didn\u2019t really cook, but it was very handy to have the kitchen facilities available to prepare food. The terraces outside were an added bonus - hummingbirds visited the potted citrus trees that were in flower. \r\nCoyoac\u00e1n is a lovely historical peaceful area of Mexico City & the locals were amazingly friendly & helpful to us as we bumbled around not speaking any Spanish!  The apartment is around the corner from Frida Khalo\u2019s Casa Azul & is only a couple of blocks from the market & main squares at the centre of Coyoac\u00e1n & the Museo Nacional de las Culturas Populares. We found there were plenty of taxis to take us to the centre of Mexico City & the airport.\r\nWe loved staying here & would recommend the apartment for its comfort, peacefulness & convenience, & will definitely check out its availability when we return to Mexico City.\r\n"
