                    "reviewerid": "30517455",
                    "reviewer_name": "Piotr",
                    "comments": "The apartment is a little far from the old center,  a 20 min walk to the subway. Subway only 5$ each journey and easy to use.  \n The apartment is  comfortable and has a very well equipt kitchen, little terrace area, within a complex of other apartments and a office area next door, spiral staircases to each level.\n The water worked well and plenty of hot water, sprays from the shower onto the floor otherwise wonderful.  Use of washing machine and a place to hangout to dry.\nWiFi worked OK, the router was in the office near by. Trisha was friendly and helped with any problems and suggestions of places to go.\nWe had no problems and enjoyed our stay here, lovely flowers and extra thoughtful things in the apartment.  The only problem was the floor, it was hard to keep clean.   We were able to park on the street and had no problem with a parking space outside the house.   \nFrida Kahlo Museum just around the corner."
