                    "reviewerid": "16921120",
                    "reviewer_name": "Derek",
                    "comments": "This condo is an excellent spot, centrally located just outside La Condesa, but within easy walking distance of all the essentials in the area (grocery, taqueria, etc). \n\nEverywhere else is easily-reached by Uber for very cheap (local Mexico City taxis seem to charge exorbitant rates, especially if you exhibit gringo characteristics).\n\nGabriella was our contact person for the condo, and was unbelievably amazing. Her responses were prompt, professional, and exceedingly helpful. After one member of our group had their luggage delayed, she offered to have it delivered to her so we didn't have to stick around the condo to wait for it. She was an indispensable part of our experience here.\n\nThe condo itself is very stylish but also functional. The second floor is accessible only by a flight of stairs. There is a closet full of various toiletry items at the top of the second floor which was also helpful. Beds were comfortable and towels were fluffy.\n\nEntry into the house was via a series of locked doors, each with their own key. This got a bit confusing at times but we appreciated the added security measures.\n\nOverall, would definitely recommend this spot for a stay for a large group in CDMX!"
