                    "comments": "First things first, this house is amazing!!! It has three stories!! With a roof top patio on the third story. There is so much room for a large family to stay there. We were a party of 6 and had almost too much room. Lol!! The house is decorated beautifully and is very clean. There is a housekeeper there everyday to clean and upkeep the house. She is sweet and unobtrusive. We had her make breakfast for us one day for a fee of $35USD for the 6 of us. We asked for chilaquiles. They were the best with homemade refried beans!!! My sister in law couldn\u2019t stop saying how amazing they were!! We did opt to have someone pick us up at the airport in their Suburban. It cost $35USD one way from the airport. An UBER probably would\u2019ve been cheaper but it was nice having us all together in one vehicle. The location of the house is good. It\u2019s too far from Downtown to walk but UBER is easy and cheap to use. There are many restaurants and grocery stores near by the house to eat if you don\u2019t want to go all the way downtown. I would definitely recommend this place if you are spending some days in Mexico City."
