                    "comments": "Things aren't in an ideal state, light bulbs are missing all over the place, cushions on the living room are worn down and broken up, light contacts are all messed up, no blackout curtains, just translucid ones that might invade your privacy at all times and disrupt your sleep and don't even work well when closing, some dinner chairs are broke, they come apart if not handled with extra care, look not to touch, no microwave, the extra bedroom has a bathroom that is used as storage, so it's unvailable for use, the guest bathroom has spiders and no lights, and the main bathroom didn't had any toilet paper, the marble walls and sink are cracked and the drainage on the shower cabin doesn't work properly, the paint of the ceiling on the kitchen area is coming apart with strips falling on top of your head, and the cherry top was that the apartment had this obviously old smell, so I had to pay extra cleaning to come and vacuum the place, and I got stolen and didn't want to jump into conclusions till I was sure of it, wrote on (Hidden by Airbnb) to the owner to plead my case and in order for him to investigate, he just replied that things weren't on the apartment and blocked me. All bad things could've gone away if he had the cordiality to take things into matter in a more professional way, but he didn't. Overall experience, bad bad bad. Disappointing with a good location and great possibilities if they care about important details and stuff like mainte0ce and some customer support."
