                    "reviewerid": "112978",
                    "reviewer_name": "Clay And Andrea",
                    "comments": "Morgana was extremely polite and helpful. Just as we arrived in Mexico City, my girlfriend lost her passport. Morgana spent a good amount of time on the phone talking to the lost and found at the airport for us.\r\n\r\nThis apartment is in a great location, the La Condesa neighborhood. We spent four days in Mexico City, and came to the conclusion that La Condesa is clearly the coolest neighborhood. You can find lots of great restaurants within a few blocks' walk. The apartment was clean and offered plenty of space.\r\n\r\nThere were a couple of minor downsides. The beds were a little on the hard side. We're now at our rental in Playa del Carmen, where the bed is nice and soft, and has a foam cushion on the top, and I'm definitely noticing the difference. Also the hot water was very temperamental. It would start off nice and hot, then get lukewarm or even coldish a few minutes later. Then you could come back 10 minutes later and it would be hot, although lasting for no more than 10 minutes. This was only really a big deal on our third day, when it got incredibly cold (in the 45 degree Fahrenheit range) and we came home soaked and cold, and just wanted to take a nice hot shower.\r\n\r\nAll things considered, this apartment is a very good value for anyone looking to stay in a cool neighborhood in Mexico City."
