                    "comments": "I've just stayed at Morgana's place for 2 weeks and couldn't have been happier. Was especially grateful for the portable heater (a luxury I've never stumbled upon in Mexico before!) and other small things, like having an iron and ironing board. For those of you travelling to DF for the first time, Condesa is a precious neighbourhood; full of beautiful 20- 30's architecture, very green and walkable. The nightlife can be a challenge in the more central part, but this apartment is situated in a more tranquil area towards Chapultepec; it's very \"local\", and super quiet at night (you will sleep like a baby ;) ) Coffee place, bike rental, laundry places right outside. And Morgana is the perfect host. Definitely recommend staying here!   "
