                    "reviewer_name": "Richard",
                    "comments": "Hi, I stayed at Francisco's apartment just near Reforma.  It is super-cool - I felt like there ought to be a model reclining in the lounge and a photographer taking pictures.  The bed is great, furnishings and everything is superb.\r\n\r\nThe location is excellent - right next to Zona Rosa, and a short walk to Condesa.  There is a great local restaurant for breakfast a few minutes walk away, on C/ London, called Do\u00f1a Blanca.  All up $47 (that's 47 pesos, = US$3.50).\r\n\r\nFrancisco was an excellent host, kept in touch and was very flexible when my arrival was delayed.  (Be warned - at busy times like Friday evening, immigration at the airport and queuing for a taxi can take a long time - it may be well worth booking a car to be waiting for your arrival.)\r\n\r\nI certainly highly recommend Francisco's apartment."
