                    "reviewerid": "159009",
                    "reviewer_name": "Leslie",
                    "comments": "Paulina's apartment is amazing: central location, clean and spacious, great wifi connection, 24-hour building security, and nice surrounding neighborhood. Her sister Gabriela was very accommodating with our early morning arrival, greeting us and showing us the apartment and building, and made suggestions on attractions for our visit. We were a party of four female adults (all family) and felt very safe and comfortable in the apartment and even outside the apartment. It was walking distance to Bellas Artes, Torre Latinoamericano, various metro stops, decent restaurants and street food vendors (I drank many licuados and jugos from vendors a block away), and we even walked all the way to Zocalo. If you need to exchange money, there is a bank in the same building but accessible from the outside.\r\n\r\nThe apartment itself met all of our needs. It truly felt like a home away from home. After days of walking around and sightseeing, it was nice to come back to the apartment to relax and unwind. Towels and soap were provided, blankets/pillows, the kitchen was equipped with basic appliances and crockery. We did not use the gym or the pool because we were out most of the day and night exploring D.F. There is a market nearby to buy food/snacks and condiments. There is no A/C in the unit however there were fans in every room which we used as the weather was somewhat humid and hot when we visited in late August.  I highly recommend this apartment for a short term or long term stay and will definitely recommend this place to friends and family. Hopefully we can visit again soon!"
