          "space": "****** CHECK OUT OUR OTHER APARTMENT IN THE SAME BUILDING ****** The apartment has one Queen size bed, and two twins. All three are real beds. it is located on the third floor.  The best supermarket in the neighborhood is across the street open from 7am-11pm, a great cheese shop bellow on the corner as well as a tasty bakery (Try the Carrot Cake or the Pear Tart). There is dry cleaning and laundry half a block away. YOU CAN ALSO CHECK OUT OUR OTHER LISTING: http://www.airbnb.com/rooms/198778",
          "description": "Yet another comfy Apartment smack in the middle the Colonia Condesa, one of the hippest neighborhoods in Mexico City. A short 10 minute walk from the museums in the Bosque de Chapultepec (Museo de Arte Moderno, Museo Tamayo, Castillo de Chapultepec, etc.), as well as from the Colonia Roma. A 5 minute walk from El Parque Mexico. ****** CHECK OUT OUR OTHER APARTMENT IN THE SAME BUILDING ****** The apartment has one Queen size bed, and two twins. All three are real beds. it is located on the third floor.  The best supermarket in the neighborhood is across the street open from 7am-11pm, a great cheese shop bellow on the corner as well as a tasty bakery (Try the Carrot Cake or the Pear Tart). There is dry cleaning and laundry half a block away. YOU CAN ALSO CHECK OUT OUR OTHER LISTING: http://www.airbnb.com/rooms/198778 The apartment has: - two bedrooms, one with a queen bed, and the other with two twin beds - fully equipped kitchen with four burner gas stove and oven, toaster over, microwa",
          "neighborhood_overview": "A short 10 minute walk from the museums in the Bosque de Chapultepec (Museo de Arte Moderno, Museo Tamayo, Castillo de Chapultepec, etc.), as well as from the Colonia Roma. A 5 minute walk from El Parque Mexico. The best supermarket in the neighborhood is across the street open from 7am-11pm, a great cheese shop bellow on the corner as well as a tasty bakery (Try the Carrot Cake or the Pear Tart). There is dry cleaning and laundry half a block away.",
          "notes": "The apartment is basic, but well equipped, please let me know if you have special needs, and we will try to comply.  The building is located in front of a supermarket with 24hr floodlights",
          "transit": "Transportation The apartment is 4 blocks away from the Juanacatlan subway stop and 6 from the Chapultepec stop. Both stations are on the same transit line that takes you downtown to the Centro Historico. Transit to other subway lines is on station away at Tacubaya station, or 4 stations to Salto del Agua. Ecobici bike service station located across the street. Uber is also a very good option. If you have a car, you can park it at the public parking lot one block away. Not sure of the price.",
          "access": "The apartment has: - two bedrooms, one with a queen bed, and the other with two twin beds - fully equipped kitchen with four burner gas stove and oven, toaster over, microwave, refrigerator and freezer, Nikken water filter, sink  - one bathroom with shower, toilet and sink.  - Living area with a double and a single couches, and a table for six. - We can provide a pack and play crib if you like.  - Wifi",
          "interaction": "Feel free to contact us via AirBnb or watsapp for any censers or problems. We try to always be available. I can organize for a privet driver to pick you up at the airport just out of customs, with the apartment keys. He charges $30us. If you have a late or very early arrival, this is the best options. The housekeeper can also meet you at the apartment between 9am and 5pm.",
          "house_rules": "- Please do not drink water from the faucet. I will provide bottled water for drinking  - Please try to leave the kitchen clean at night, we don't want to attract creepy crawlers  - No smoking please, no parties.  - No pets allowed  - If you have any problem, gas, water, wifi, let me know immediately so I can do something about it.  - A couple times a year we experience water shortage. There is a water jug in the bathroom for emergencies, flushing toilets, etc. pleas keep it full.",
