                    "reviewerid": "317592",
                    "reviewer_name": "Elissa",
                    "comments": "The apartment is a perfect place for exploring Condesa and Chapultepec Park. We immediately felt a part of the neighborhood and its rhythm - getting our delicious croissant or baguette for the day from Pastiserrie Po (across the street); our perfect mangos from the fruit vendor in front of the apartment; our quesadillas at the corner and fresh tortillas one shop further... All the parks are within walking distance. Our kids loved the playgrounds and libraries at Parque Espana and Mexico. The apartment itself is clean, bright and lovely. Morgana and Omar were very responsive. We certainly hope to be back!"
