                    "reviewerid": "13380318",
                    "reviewer_name": "Hector",
                    "comments": "I stayed at Eugenia's place for the month of June. I stayed in the one bedroom and shared one bathroom with another renter.\r\n\r\nThroughout my stay Eugenia made sure that I had everything I needed. Since I arrived with an ankle injury she was extra helpful to make sure I was comfortable and didn't re-injure myself.\r\n\r\nThere were other medical students that stayed there while I lived at Eugenia's. Everyone was respectful of common spaces and everyone was friendly.\r\n\r\nThe area was also very pleasant. I never felt unsafe in the neighborhood. Her house is at the end of a cul-de-sac and it is very quiet. Two doors down you can drop-off laundry and purchase water and other snacks. Two blocks away is a main thoroughfare where you can find a convenience store and a decent gym.\r\n\r\nThe house is near all hospitals in the area as well as downtown Tlalpan. In downtown Tlalpan you can find a lively town square with a traditional Mexican market, a church, and several cafes, restaurants, bars and bookstores. \r\n\r\nI would stay there again if I needed to and I would definitely recommend it to a friend. \r\n\r\n-H"
