                    "reviewerid": "40114663",
                    "reviewer_name": "Jarl",
                    "comments": "Great studio apartment! Great location! The apartment: apartment is on the second floor. Lots of light and windows. Nice little kitchen that was totally stocked with everything you would need to cook meals. Bathroom was great. Very nice hot water. Had no problems with water at all. The tub is small but fine for showering. Nice tv and dvd player. Internet was great. They had the username and password ready for us when we arrived. There is a gated entrance so you feel very safe. One of the great things about the apartment was the silence at night. My wife and I have traveled quite a bit in central and South America. Great weather but that tends to mean very little insulation. Any outside noise is going to come in. This place was great. You could hear life during the day, but it was normal levels of activity but at night it was totally quiet from about 10pm to 7am. That was wonderful! They had bottled water, fresh fruit, fresh pastries, fresh cut flowers for us when we arrived! There is a doorman there from 7am-6pm. His name was Luis. Very nice young man. The location: it really can't get much better than this. This was my wife and my first time in Mexico City. The apartment is situated ideally. You can walk all over the place and feel totally safe. Some of the things that we loved: flower kiosks with incredibly cheap prices (my wife loves calla lilies - in the states these can range from $4-$7/stem but we found them for 35 pesos for ten! The exchange rate was 16.5pesos/$1! So basically $2.25 for ten! And they were huge. Needless to say I looked like a hero to my wife and it barely cost me), local restaurants everywhere, panaderias (fresh baked bread stores with fresh pastries - breakfast every morning - delicious but horrible for the (Website hidden by Airbnb) was worth it), subway about 4 blocks away ($0.33/ride - yes that is right, thirty three cents, 5 pesos, to ride the subway - and it can take you anywhere), uber taxis - if you don't have the uber app get it, it can't be any easier. You set your account up on your phone. When you are ready for a taxi you open the app and request an uber. They always picked us up in less than 4min! When you are done the fare is charged automatically to the card on the account - always fair, always honest. We would normally head out in the morning and use the subway and hiking to get anywhere. Then when we were tired at night we would get an uber back. Sandro: Sandro communicated in a great way. Always responded to questions. Set things up for us so that when we arrived someone was there to get us the keys. Overall an excellent experience. My brother and his wife live inMexico city so they know the area very well. They tend to be..."
