                    "comments": "For several years Sandro\u2019s apartment has been my \u201cgo to\u201d Airbnb whenever I\u2019m in Mexico City. I am a part-time resident of Mexico and have a house in a city 3 hours away. Sandro is an excellent communicator, the apartment generally has a good aesthetic and good architecture. And it\u2019s a great location that feels safe. Unfortunately, after my last 3 night stay, I must agree with the last reviewer\u2019s honest and accurate criticisms. A large, extended family has apparently moved into the adjacent apartment. The noise from that apartment reverberated throughout the small courtyard until well after midnight each night. It gets really loud at times. I would also agree that there are some quality control issues with whoever is cleaning the apartment. Furthermore, the balcony floorboards are loose and appear to be rotting. In any case, what used to be a pleasant, quiet spot for enjoying morning coffee no longer feels  pleasant, quiet or even safe. My previous reviews of Sandro\u2019s apartment have all be very positive. In fairness to Airbnb users,  I am sad that I can no longer give this apartment the high rating it once deserved."
